  "texts": [
    "Measuring researcher impact.",
    "In evaluating the unique impact of a researcher, one could lower the weight of a paper as a function of the number of coauthors.",
    "For example, a single-authored paper should be counted as 1 publication whereas a 3-author paper could be counted as a third of a publication.",
    "Yet, in evaluating the network of that researcher-how central and well-connected they are-one should give more weight to papers with more coauthors, and give more weight to more connected coauthors (i.e., a well-connected coauthor \"helps\" this index).",
    "One benefit of the proposed approach is its simplicity, as it is easy to explain and understand."
  ],
